==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Constructiveness
<hw>Con*struct"ive*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Tendency or
ability to form or construct.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Phren.)</fld> <def>The faculty which enables one to
construct, as in mechanical, artistic, or literary matters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Constructor</ent>⟦br⟧
